AttributeList.Text: This block calls all the logic required for the Tank Level Indication.

Precision Calibration with Pressure calibrator attached to sensor. Upper = 2100mm of H20 @ 20C Lower = 100mm of H20 @ 20C RawCaptureDiff (@2000mm) = UpperRaw(@2100mm)-LowerRaw(@100mm) RawCaptureRange = 2100mm-100mm =2000mm

Rough Calibration based on a sounding RoughCalRangemmSG1(calibration range for H2O@20C) = Sounding in mm/ Specific Gravity or Fluid (This will be reaccounted for when doing the level calculation after calibration) Subtract the offset from the sensor face to the bottom (this should be measured and never adjusted), it is not measured by the sensor Subtract from this range the sensor low value example -100mm to get the range of the calibration that the sensor is currently measuring Take the current measured range raw and divided by the current raw input value

Y=MX+B where Y is the level (H2O@20C) , X is the Raw Value, M is the mm/Raw, B is the offset (mm) from the bottom (not measured by the sensor) + lower range of the sensor Then we convert the level to %

There are 5 tables for Trim Adjustment. Level, 2 FWD and 2 AFT. If the "Setpoint" for that table is set to "0", then it will not be used. The table is for that trim is used when the Trim is equal to, or above the Setpoint in that table for 1s.
